<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-39-0388 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper presents a personal view of the role of nuclear power in electricitygeneration. The capital and running costs of a nuclear power stationare discussed, along with the costs of electricity, nuclear power asan energy source, performance of the nuclear power industry, and someengineering features of the nuclear reactor. The author speculates asto the future demand for electricity in the United Kingdom, and proposesthe idea of domestic generators to supply domestic heating in the nextcentury. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>